{"session_id":"e5f7854c-c5bd-458f-8330-eb27e01ab0d6","transcript_path":"/Users/jakovivancek/.claude/projects/-Users-jakovivancek-Desktop-Jakov-Ivancek-projekt/e5f7854c-c5bd-458f-8330-eb27e01ab0d6.jsonl","cwd":"/Users/jakovivancek/Desktop/Jakov_Ivancek_projekt","prompt_id":"71a79742-2821-464c-baf4-79d16629314b","permission_mode":"auto","effort":{"level":"high"},"hook_event_name":"Stop","stop_hook_active":false,"last_assistant_message":"Fixed and verified. Summary:\n\n**Root cause**: `.github/hooks/stop_hook.py` (the script every hook config points to) parsed transcript entries expecting other tools' formats (`user.message`/`assistant.message` from VS Code Copilot, `USER_INPUT`/`PLANNER_RESPONSE` from Antigravity/Gemini). Real Claude Code transcripts use `type: \"user\"`/`\"assistant\"` with the actual payload nested in `message.content` — a list of blocks (`text`, `thinking`, `tool_use`, `tool_result`, `document`). None of the old cases matched, so every run silently produced a 4-line stub with just the header and no conversation — which is exactly what your `agent_logs/chat_*.md` files looked like.\n\n**Fix**: added a new parser branch for Claude Code's actual schema to both `stop_hook.py` and `stop_hook.ps1` (kept the old branches so other tools still work if you use them):\n- Real user text and attached-file mentions get logged under `## User`.\n- Assistant replies get logged under `## AI Assistant`.\n- `thinking` blocks are skipped (internal reasoning, not conversation).\n- Tool-result-only synthetic \"user\" turns (the automatic feedback after each tool call) are skipped so the log isn't noise.\n- Tool calls are logged as `- **Tool call:** ToolName`.\n\n**Verified**: piped this session's real transcript through the fixed `stop_hook.py` directly — went from a 6-line stub to 4245 lines of actual conversation. Regenerated `agent_logs/chat_2026-07-02_e5f7854c-...md` for this session so it's no longer broken. I couldn't execute-test the `.ps1` variant since PowerShell isn't installed on this Mac — the logic mirrors the Python fix exactly, but flag it if you run into issues on Windows.\n\nThe `.claude/settings.json` wiring itself was already correct — `.agents/hooks.json` and `.github/hooks/settings.json` are messy/duplicated but harmless, since Claude Code doesn't read either of those (only `.claude/settings.json`); I left them alone since they may still matter for other tools you use.","background_tasks":[],"session_crons":[]}


