{"session_id":"e5f7854c-c5bd-458f-8330-eb27e01ab0d6","transcript_path":"/Users/jakovivancek/.claude/projects/-Users-jakovivancek-Desktop-Jakov-Ivancek-projekt/e5f7854c-c5bd-458f-8330-eb27e01ab0d6.jsonl","cwd":"/Users/jakovivancek/Desktop/Jakov_Ivancek_projekt","prompt_id":"e454b36b-300c-457f-b04f-b228813e903a","permission_mode":"auto","effort":{"level":"high"},"hook_event_name":"Stop","stop_hook_active":false,"last_assistant_message":"Everything is clean and green. Here's the summary of this refactoring pass.\n\n## What was cleaned up\n\n**Dead code removed:**\n- `Program.cs`: unused `sqliteBuilder`/`dbPath` computation (assigned, never read).\n- Fixed the last build warning: `KnownNetworks` → `KnownIPNetworks` (obsolete API, same behavior).\n\n**Duplication reduced:**\n- Stripped `using System;`, `System.Linq;`, `System.Collections.Generic;`, `System.Threading.Tasks;`, `System.IO;`, `System.Threading;`, `System.Net.Http;` from 34 files — all already provided by the project's `ImplicitUsings`, so these were pure redundant clutter (verified against the SDK-generated global-usings file first). Zero behavior change; every removal is a no-op for the compiler.\n- `HotelsController`/`Program.cs` used fully-qualified `HotelMgt.Web.Services.IAttachmentService` instead of a `using` + short name, inconsistent with the rest of the codebase — fixed.\n- `AttachmentService`: the web-root-path resolution expression was duplicated across two methods — extracted into a private `WebRootPath` property.\n\n**Consistency improved:**\n- `FormModels.cs` and `UiModels.cs` were the only two files still using old block-scoped `namespace X { }`; converted to file-scoped `namespace X;` (and dedented), matching every other file in the project.\n- Trailing blank line inside `PaymentMethod` enum removed.\n- Renamed `resetConnection`/`resetCommand` in `Program.cs` to `pragmaConnection`/`pragmaCommand` — they don't reset anything, they just enable the SQLite foreign-key pragma.\n\n**Zombie files/folders deleted:**\n- `.tmp/` — self-labeled \"Temporary verification helper,\" three near-duplicate one-line wrappers around `dotnet test`.\n- Fixed a stale `sitemap.md` that documented routes from an earlier English-route version of the app (`/hotels`, `/rooms`, …) that no longer exist — rewrote it to match the actual current Croatian routes (`/hoteli`, `/smjestaji`, …) and added the entries that were missing (AI assistant, API resources, Setup pages).\n- Added `.gitignore` entry for `__pycache__/` and removed a stray cache dir left by my own verification.\n\nEvery change was verified with a full solution rebuild (0 warnings, 0 errors) and the complete test suite (58 xUnit + 1 Playwright E2E, all passing) after each batch of edits.\n\n## Left unchanged (on purpose)\n\n- **The 8 nearly-identical CRUD API controllers and 8 nearly-identical CRUD MVC controllers.** Real duplication, but collapsing them into a generic base controller is an architectural rewrite, not a cleanup — it would touch routing, DTO validation, and `CreatedAtAction` semantics across every entity, which is exactly the \"large rewrite\" risk you told me to avoid.\n- **`Hotel-Mgt.Console/Program.cs`'s `RunOriginalDemo()`** (~500 lines of in-memory LINQ demo data). It looks like leftover scaffolding from an earlier lab, but it's still the actual, reachable default behavior when the console app runs without `--mcp` — deleting it would change observable behavior, which the brief explicitly rules out.\n- **`.agents/hooks.json` and `.github/hooks/settings.json`** — genuinely messy (duplicated blocks, many redundant event-name variants), but I don't know which of those variant names some other tool you use actually depends on, so I couldn't verify a trim wouldn't silently break logging for that tool.\n- **`Lab5.md`** (1690 lines) — an unreferenced historical grading spec for an already-completed lab. Strong zombie-file candidate, but deleting that much content is a judgment call about whether you want to keep it as a record — flagging it rather than removing it myself.\n- **Entity constructor style** (constructor-based `null!` init vs. `Attachment`'s inline `= null!`) — both valid, purely cosmetic, not worth the diff.\n- **Razor views** — didn't restructure shared markup across the `_XTable.cshtml`/`_XForm.cshtml` partials; UI-behavior risk there is higher and harder for me to verify without a browser pass, so I left them as-is.","background_tasks":[],"session_crons":[]}


